<br>
First, everyone here on this message board above the age of 12 knows what is being depicted there; and any other interpretation is either a dillusion or an attempt at humor.  The picture is depicting anal sex between the two guys.<br>
<br>
Second, this sig was created to elicit controversy.  Any reasonable person posting that sig on a public message board would expect that a decent percentage of the community would be upset over the sig.<br>
<br>
I personally think this signature and Ilmarin's linked signature are inappropriate as they are depictions of the sexual act itself.  We know there are many kids who come and read these message boards and I don't think it is appropriate viewing.  <br>
<br>
I agree with Caliopae; I think this would get harsher criticism if it was a female whose neck was being grabbed onto instead of a male.  At first glance, the signature bothered me and it had nothing to do with the genders depicted.  The guy on the right has his hands on the neck of the guy to the left and it looks like the guy to the left is crying.  It could be a consensual encounter but my first reaction is it looked like the guy on the right was raping the guy on the left.  <br>
<br>
Gio's right to free speech isn't really relevant here.  The protections of the First Amendment don't apply to a private messageboard (which this is).  If the mods feel this signature goes against the norms of decency, they can ban it.  If I were a moderator, it would be an easy decision for me to ban that as well as Ilmarin's sig.<br>
